MAIN PATTERN IS OF "HEAP-SIZE", WE CARE OF THE SIZE OF HEAP. 

For every element:-

If heap size < k
push

If current element bigger than heap top
pop (THE CURRENT TOP AND REMOVE IT)
push (THE NEW BIGGER ELEMENT WE GOT)

Otherwise ignore.

CODE-
class Solution {
public:
    int kthLargestElement(vector<int>& nums, int k) {

      priority_queue<int,vector<int>,greater<int>> minHeap;

      for(int num:nums){
        if(minHeap.size() < k){

            minHeap.push(num);
        }
        else if(num> minHeap.top()){
            minHeap.pop();
            minHeap.push(num);
        }
      }

return minHeap.top();



    }
};
